
start:
make directory
install pipenv, django 
    pipenv install
    pipenv install django
check version
    pipenv run python -m django --version
view django admin commands
    pipenv run django-admin 
create project
    pipenv run django-admin startproject blog_django_project

fileoverview:
blog_django_project
    __init__.py 
    settings.py (settings)
    urls.py (url routing)
    wsgi.py (how our python web app and the web server communicate (not touching))
manage.py (file that allows us to run command line commands (no changes to be made))

start server 
    pipenv run python manage.py runserver 

create app
    pipenv run python manage.py startapp blog 


open views.py 
    from django.http import HttpResponse 
create a home function 
(going to handle the traffic from the home page of our blog)
(going to take in a request argument and return what we want the user to see when they're sent to this route)
(this is where the logic goes for how we want to handle certain routes)
    def home(request):
        return HttpResponse('<h1>Blog Home</h1>')
(need to map URL pattern to this view function)
create a new bot module in our blog directory called urls.py and in that file is where we'll map the urls that we want to correspond to each view function
open this urls.py 
    from django.urls import path 

    urlpatterns = [
        path('', views.home, name='blog-home'),
    ]







